body:
**Description**
I am using SkiaSharp to generate an image that represent a transaction receipt that can be shared via my Xamarin app.  When I try to convert the SKData to array I get an error message:
{System.MethodAccessException: Method `System.ReadOnlySpan`1[System.Byte]..ctor(void*,int)' is inaccessible from method `SkiaSharp.SKData.AsSpan()'
 The code bellow works fine with the Android version of the app, both not with iOS.


**Code**

        public static byte[] GenerateImage(ImageReceipt imageReceipt)
        {
            FontFamilyName = ImageReceipt.FontFamilyName;
            SKBitmap bitmap = GetReceiptBitmap(imageReceipt);
            using (SKImage image = SKImage.FromBitmap(bitmap))
            using (SKData data = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 80))
            {
                return data.ToArray();
            }
        }

*Expected Behavior**

Return the Byte Array 

Exception : {System.MethodAccessException: Method `System.ReadOnlySpan`1[System.Byte]..ctor(void*,int)' is inaccessible from method `SkiaSharp.SKData.AsSpan()'


<!-- a general description of what really happened -->

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  1.68.1.1
- Last known good version:  N/A
- IDE:   Visual Studio 
  - Android:8.1
  - iOS:  12.4.0.64
